===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|bronze script}} from the {{w|Western Zhou period}}, it was originally an {{Han compound|ls=ic|nocap=1|宀|t1=house|頁|t2=head}} — only one person in the house; alone.

In the bronze script from the {{w|Warring States period}}, two decorative strokes were added around {{zh-l|*頁}}. The seal script found in ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' adds two additional strokes, making the component under {{zh-l|*宀}} appear as {{zh-l|*分}} and {{zh-l|*頁}}, leading ''Shuowen'' to erroneously interpret the character as an {{Han compound|ls=ic|nocap=1|宀|t1=house|頒|t2=to distribute}}.

===Etymology===
Related to {{och-l|鰥|widower}}, {{och-l|孤|orphan; alone}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Cognate with {{cog|bo|དགོན་པ||solitary place; desert; wilderness}}, {{cog|bo|སྒོས||private; individual}}.

